sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1500015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: paroF, mutH are genomic XL1Blue, mCherry is from distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick contains mutH() and mCherry under the control of the tyrosine-sensitive promoter paroF. Unless the E. coli cell produces very high levels of tyrosine, the mutagenizing protein mutH() and mCherry will be produced. The mCherry is used as a reporter to indicate when this maximum tyrosine production is reached. mutH should cause genomic mutations that should result in the cell eventually producing high levels of tyrosine.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Beckner

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1500001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry-LVA (BBa_J06505) was used and came from the registry plasmid. ParoF was cloned from wild-type DH5-alpha E. coli genomic sequence. RBS.3 (BBa_B0032) sequence originally came from the registry and was designed directly into primer overhangs for mCherry-LVA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A plasmid that contains the tyrosine-repressible promoter ParoF, followed by an RBS (RBS.3, medium strength) and mCherry-LVA as a reporter gene directly downstream. We used it to insert our combinations of mutator genes directly downstream of the ParoF promoter, forming the actuator module of our project which contains an optimized promoter, a reporter, and one or more mutators. The transcription factor TyrR can bind to ParoF and repress it when itself bound to tyrosine.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to insert mutator genes downstream of the mCherry-LVA, we would cut open the two downstream restriction sites, with corresponding cuts on the mutator genes, before ligating the insert and this plasmid together.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kevin Yang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1500996
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: E. coli (MG1655) genomic and quickchanged to E56A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mutagenized mutH useful as a mutagen protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Beckner

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1500999
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cloned from wild-type DH5-alpha E. coli genomic sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Used in BBa_1500001, this promoter drives expression of the AroF promoter in wild-type E. coli. Here, it is used as a tyrosine-repressible promoter sensitive to the transcription factor TyrR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kevin Yang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry from Roger Y. Tsien's lab, altered to be BioBrick compatible and with an LVA tag added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP (DsRed) derived, altered to be a biobrick by removing a PstI site and adding in the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made a point mutation to eliminate a PstI site in the middle and then added BioBrick ends with the LVA tag using PCR.

Sequenced using primers that bind to the pSB1A2 plasmid on either side of the brick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ytwang
